item.title: Deal?
item.media:title: Deal?
item.media:description:
My name is Brian. I have recently turned 24. This is my story.

I knew I shouldn't have trusted those guys but hey, desperate times call for desperate measures. It wasn't a big amount and I was late only by 2 days. I told her I would pay her back as soon as I can with interest even. She said it would be fine.

Yesterday night, while I was sleeping, they broke the back door. I woke up only to be hit on the head and lose my consciousness for a brief moment. Well, at least it felt like it.

I woke up in an unknown room with the door locked. Just as I approached it, the guard had begun to unlock it - took him quite a few seconds.

-You are coming with me.

I followed the guard as I had no intention to quarrel with that massive headache I've got due to last night's knockout.

He led me to a room with a table in the middle. While I sat down he cuffed my hands to a metal attachment so I couldn't leave the table. I felt helpless, cuffed to the table like that with shackles around my bare feet. Several guards watched while I was waiting for their boss. In about 15 minutes, she entered the room.

-I told you I don't tolerate lateness.

As I was trying to explain myself, she hit me in the face, letting me know it's not my turn to talk.

-Spare me your lies, I couldn't care less. Even if you had the money we would have kidnapped you. I had my eyes on you the very first time we met. Young, well built and handsome. I want a pet like you. You are mine now.

She waved to one of the guards who unlocked the cuffs from the table only to put more chains on.

-Take him through the process.
